  "prompt": "How much money do I owe my housemate?",
  "response": "To determine how much money you owe your housemate, you would need to provide specific details. Here are a few things to consider:\n\n1. **Shared Expenses:** List any shared expenses such as rent, utilities, groceries, or other household costs. Include the total amount and each person's share.\n2. **Previous Payments:** Consider any payments you have already made towards these shared expenses and compare them to your agreed-upon share.\n3. **Personal Borrowing:** Account for any personal loans or borrowing between you and your housemate.\n\nOnce you have all the relevant information, add up your share of the expenses and subtract any payments you have already made. The remaining amount will be what you owe.\n\nFeel free to provide specific details if you need help calculating the amount.",
